# DataVeritas — Complete Project Walkthrough

## What Is This Project?

**DataVeritas** is an **Enterprise Data Quality & Trust Platform** built with **Streamlit**. It lets users upload any CSV/Excel dataset (or generate synthetic data) and instantly get a comprehensive quality audit with scores, visualizations, and actionable insights.

> **Live app**: https://dataveritas.streamlit.app/

---

## Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Frontend / App Framework | **Streamlit** |
| Data Processing | **Pandas**, **NumPy** |
| Visualization | **Plotly**, **Matplotlib**, **Seaborn** |
| Fuzzy Matching | **RapidFuzz** |
| Outlier Detection | **scikit-learn** (Isolation Forest) |
| Synthetic Data | **Faker** |
| Interactivity | **streamlit_plotly_events** |

---

## How The App Works (User Flow)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["Load Dataset<br/>(Upload CSV/Excel or Generate)"] --> B["Data Preview"]
    B --> C{"Navigate Sidebar"}
    C --> D["Trust Score"]
    C --> E["Value Distribution Audit"]
    C --> F["Cardinality Audit"]
    C --> G["Duplicates Audit"]
    C --> H["Nulls / Completeness Audit"]
    C --> I["Anomaly / Outlier Audit"]
    C --> J["Consistency Rule Engine (BETA)"]
    C --> K["Entity Resolution / Merger (BETA)"]
    C --> L["Dataset Drift Detector (BETA)"]
```

1. **Load data** — Upload a `.csv` or `.xlsx` file, or generate synthetic test data (100–200K rows) using Faker
2. **Preview** — Browse data with column filtering
3. **Run audits** — Navigate the sidebar to 7 different quality audits + 3 tools

